The paper deals with the problem of streaming XML transformations, which is a common task in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also presents a transducer model for XQuery, which is a programming language used for querying and transforming XML data (cs.PL). The use of functional programming optimizations, such as strictness analysis and deforestation, is also mentioned, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a prototype implementation of the streaming engine, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
